---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Engineering Excellence"
  dekStrong="For engineers who care about the craft."
  dek="Engineering Excellence is a long-form journal of practice for senior engineers, tech leads, and engineering managers inside large organizations."
  withSidebar={false}
>
  <div class="max-w-[40rem] mx-auto px-8 py-12 lg:py-16">
    <h1 class="font-sans font-medium text-ink text-[clamp(1.8rem,3vw,2.4rem)] leading-tight tracking-[-0.02em] m-0 mb-8">
      About
    </h1>

    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <p>
        Engineering Excellence publishes essays on the craft of building software at scale —
        leadership, best practices, career growth, and what AI changes in the work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Pithy engineering advice — "shield your team," "think like a staff engineer,"
        "AI will change everything" — usually contains a real signal, but loses precision
        in the abstraction. Each essay works through the conditions under which the advice
        holds, where it breaks down, and what to do at the boundary.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every essay is grounded in sources — usually books on engineering leadership,
        organizational behavior, or career strategy. The bibliography is in the sidebar of
        the reading list so you can check the thinking yourself.
      </p>
      <p>
        Written by <strong>Robert</strong> on his own time. New essays roughly monthly.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
